  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. It&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"italic\">p</span> represents the period of the ocean wave, so the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"s equals, three halves p \"></span> can be solved for <span class=\"italic\">p</span> to represent the period of the wave in terms of the speed of the wave. Multiplying both sides of the equation by the reciprocal of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"three halves\"></span> will isolate <span class=\"italic\">p</span>. This yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"two thirds s equals, two thirds times, three halves p\"></span>, which simplifies to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"two thirds s, equals p\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"p equals, two thirds s\"></span>.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may result from errors made when rearranging the equation to solve for <span class=\"italic\">p</span>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
